label: Math Proficiency by Socio-Economic Status
note: The dataset uses rescaled indices of economic, social, and cultural status (ESCS) for trend analysis provided by the OECD: those of the years 2000, 2003, 2006, and 2009 have been harmonized to 2015, those of 2012, 2015 and 2018 to 2022.
source: Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development (OECD), Program for International Student Assessment (PISA), 2000, 2003, 2006, 2009, 2012, 2015, 2018, and 2022 Reading and Mathematics Assessments.

definition.L1: At Level 1, students can answer questions involving simple contexts where all information needed is present, and the questions are clearly defined.
definition.L2: At Level 2, students can recognize situations where they need to design simple strategies to solve problems.
definition.L3: At Level 3, students can devise solution strategies, including strategies that require sequential decision-making or flexibility.
definition.L4: At Level 4, students can work effectively with explicit models for complex concrete situations, sometimes involving two variables.
definition.L5: At Level 5, students can develop and work with models for complex situations, identifying or imposing constraints.
definition.L6: At Level 6, students can work through abstract problems and demonstrate creativity and flexible thinking.

definition.MS: Mathematical performance, for PISA, measures the mathematical literacy of a 15-year-old to formulate, employ and interpret mathematics in a variety of contexts to describe, predict and explain phenomena, recognizing the role that mathematics plays in the world. Scores are reported on a scale from 0 to 1000, the mean across OECD countries is set at 500 and the standard deviation at 100.
definition.FD: A specification of the way in which the frequencies of members of a population are distributed according to the values of the variates which they exhibit. For observed data, the distribution is usually specified in tabular form, with some grouping for continuous variates.
